    <item>
      <title>Tiny Bleeps</title>
      <link>https://sdhizumi.com/ja/works/tinybleeps/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Apr 2023 00:00:00 +0900</pubDate>
      <guid>https://sdhizumi.com/ja/works/tinybleeps/</guid>
      <description>[RELEASE] M3-2023 Spring - &lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://sdhizumi.com/img/works/tinybleeps.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Experience minimal bleep loop music made with source files limited to 1266 bytes!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This album was made with FAMIC on USB.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The source files (MML) are included as a bonus for people who purchase the album. (They are not included for single track purchases.)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What is FAMIC on USB?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;FAMIC on USB is a melody IC that can be written in MML. It was created by Prioris LLC. in Japan. It has sine, pulse, triangle, saw, 1-bit noise, and wave ram sound generators. Like with the FC/NES and GB, you can write any MML sequences up to the 1266-byte limit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
